# Rebuild HQ Doctrine

You are working from the `rebuild-hq` repo — a standalone repository for agent skills and doctrine. Read `CLAUDE.md` at the repo root for full orientation.

## Repo map

**This repo (`rebuild-hq`):** agent skills (`.claude/skills/`) and doctrine only.

**Sibling repos** (separate git remotes, not tracked by rebuild-hq):

| Path | App | Abbr |
|------|-----|------|
| `apps/rs/` | RolliSuite | RS |
| `apps/rw/` | RolliWorking | RW |
| `apps/rc/` | RolliConnect | RC |
| `apps/rt/` | RolliTime | RT |
| `apps/aa/` | Authenticator | AA |
| `documentation/` | Domain docs + all decisions (D-001–D-014) | — |
| *(planned)* | Jarvis | — |

App repos: work on `test` branch; cherry-pick verified commits to `main`.

## Skills (`.claude/skills/`)

Invoke the matching skill before starting work:

- `mapping-legacy-workflows` — document existing behavior
- `modeling-canonical-data` — schema design
- `generating-task-packets` — bounded executor briefs
- `reviewing-prs-governance` — PR/commit review
- `orchestrating-cutover-tests` — cutovers and promotions

## Non-negotiable rules

- **Surgical fix only** — touch only files listed in the task packet
- **One commit per packet** — report SHA on completion; "done" without SHA is not shipped
- **Cherry-pick verified commits** to `main` — do not merge whole `test` branches
- **Reuse-first** — search the workspace for existing assets before creating new ones
- **Ground truth** — verify DB and live behavior; never infer production state

## Before coding

1. Read `CLAUDE.md` and the relevant skill
2. Read `documentation/handoff/current.md` if touching live apps
3. Confirm task packet scope, acceptance criteria, and test commands exist

## Commits and PRs

- Do not commit unless explicitly asked
- Do not push unless explicitly asked
- Review output against `reviewing-prs-governance` before recommending merge

## Response discipline (D-009)

Keep responses short. Maximum 1–2 questions per turn.
